<MEMO>  Recipes of the Week  </MEMO>
<TEXT>  to enjoy treats made from; Scouts' annual treasures;  PASSPORT TO PLEASURE;  2
cups finely crushed <ORGANIZATION>Lemon Pastry Cremes</ORGANIZATION>;  1 cup finely chopped walnuts;  1/3
cup butter or margarine, melted; 1 quart lemon ice cream;  1 quart vanilla ice
cream;  1 cup heavy cream, whipped; 3 tablespoons crushed candy lemon drops; 
3/4 cup toasted coconut;   Combine first three ingredients, and press half of
the mixture into a 9-by-13-by-2-inch baking dish. Slightly soften ice creams,
spreading half of the vanilla and then half of the lemon over the crumb
mixture. Sprinkle with remaining half of the crumb mixture, and finish
layering with remaining vanilla and then lemon ice creams. Wrap in foil and
freeze for at least 2 hours.;    At serving time: Cut into squares or bars and
top with whipped cream. Sprinkle each piece with coconut and crushed lemon
drops.;  DAYTRIPPERS' SUSTENANCE;  5 tablespoons butter or margarine, melted; 
1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce;  1 tablespoon light brown sugar;  1/2
teaspoon garlic powder;  2 cups Golden Yangles; 2 cups popped popcorn;  2 cups
thin pretzel sticks or mini rings;  1 cup salted cocktail peanuts;   Preheat
oven to 325 degrees. In a 10-by-15-by-2-inch baking pan, combine butter,
Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar and garlic powder. Stir in <LOCATION>Golden Yangles</LOCATION>,
popcorn, pretzels and peanuts. Bake for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.; 
THAT'S THE TICKET;  10 Peanut Butter Sandwich Cookies;  5 tablespoons grape
jelly;  1 pint French vanilla ice cream, slightly softened;   Using a knife,
gently slice through each sandwich cookie so peanut butter filling stays on
one side of the cookie. Spread 10 plain cookie halves with grape jelly. Cover
each peanut butter-topped cookie with a small scoop of ice cream and top with
the other half of the cookie, jelly-side down. Push together gently and
freeze.;  WELCOME HOME PUDDING;  1 small package instant vanilla pudding;  2
cups cold milk;  1/2 cup mini marshmallows;  8 to 10 Peanut Butter Patties,
cut into small pieces;   Whipped topping;  Whole Peanut Butter Patties (for
garnish);   Prepare pudding with milk according to package directions. Fold in
marshmallows and cookies. Spoon mixture into pretty glass dishes and garnish
with a dollop of whipped topping and a whole Peanut Butter Pattie. Chill or
serve immediately.;  CHOCOLATE WHEELS;  1 cup real butter (no substitute);  2
cups sifted powdered sugar;  4 ounce unsweetened chocolate, melted and cooled;
 1 teaspoon vanilla extract;  4 eggs;  1 cup finely crushed Thin Mint cookies;
  Beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add chocolate and vanilla,
beating until well-combined. Add eggs, one at a time, beating three minutes
after each addition. Divide the cookie crumbs in half. Sprinkle half the
crumbs on the bottom of 16 cupcake papers in 1 muffin tins. Spoon chocolate
mixture over crumbs and top with remaining crumbs. Freeze until firm.; 
TRAVELER'S DELITE;  1 cup finely chopped Caramel DeLite cookies;  1/3 cup
finely chopped pecans;  1/2 cup heavy cream, whipped; 1 pint butter pecan ice
cream, softened; 1 pint chocolate ice cream, softened;   Put a 5-cup mixing
bowl in the freezer to chill, and take out ice cream to soften in the
refrigerator. Meanwhile, gently fold chopped cookies and pecans into whipped
cream and set aside. Remove bowl from freezer and carefully spoon butter pecan
ice cream over the entire surface of the bowl in a thick layer. Return to
freezer for about 15 minutes.;    Remove bowl and spoon chocolate ice cream
over butter pecan ice cream layer, leaving a hole in the middle. Return to the
freezer again about 15 minutes. Finally, fill the hole with the whipped
cream-cookie-pecan mixture, smoothing it so the bowl now has a flat, even top.
Cover with aluminum foil and freeze overnight. When ready to serve, wrap bowl
with hot, wet, towel for a few minutes. Turn over and unmold.;  MICROWAVE
JOURNEYCAKE;  1 2/3 cups finely crushed Shortbread cookies;  1 1/2 cups flour;
 3/4 cup sugar;  1 tablespoon baking powder;  1/2 teaspoon salt;  1 cup mashed
bananas;  1/2 cup milk;  1/3 cup butter or margarine, melted; 2 eggs, slightly
beaten;   In large bowl, combine cookie crumbs, flour, sugar, baking powder
and salt. In small bowl, combine bananas, milk, butter and eggs. With spoon,
stir into crumb mixture just until blended. Spoon into greased
9-by-5-by-3-inch microwave-safe loaf pan. Microwave on high 5 minutes. Rotate
pan one-quarter turn and microwave 4 to 6 minutes more, or until toothpick
inserted in center comes out clean. Let stand for 5 minutes before removing
from pan.;  LEMON CLOUD LOOKALIKES;  4 eggs, separated;  1 6-ounce can frozen
lemonade, thawed;  3/4 cup sugar;  1 1/2 teaspoon gelatin;  1/2 cup heavy
cream, whipped;  1 cup finely crushed Lemon Pastry Creme cookies;   In a
medium saucepan, blend 4 egg yolks, the can of lemonade, 1/4 cup of sugar, and
the gelatin. Stir over medium heat constantly, just until mixture simmers.
Chill, stirring occasionally, until mixture mounds when dropped from spoon.
Beat 4 egg whites at high speed until foamy. Gradually add reserved 1/2 cup of
sugar, beating mixture constantly until thick and glossy. Fold into
lemonade-gelatin mixture quickly and thoroughly; then fold in whipped cream.
Divide the cookie crumbs in half. Sprinkle one half of the crumbs on the
bottom of 16 cupcake paper in muffin tins. Spoon lemon mixture over crumbs and
top with remaining crumbs. Chill at least 3 hours.  </TEXT>
